     <table border="0" cellpadding="2" class="HP_XS" style="height:1px" width="100%">
      <tr>
       <td align="left" style="width:41%;height:18px" valign="top">
        <p style="text-align:left">
         Welcome to Retrospect Publishing.
        </p>
       </td>
       <td rowspan="2" style="width:16%;height:218px">
        <p>
         <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=3PA1">
          <img alt="Pennsylvania Published Archives on CD-ROM" height="180" src="images/covers/3PA1_30.gif" style="border:0px" width="200"/>
         </a>
        </p>
       </td>
       <td align="left" rowspan="2" style="width:44%;height:218px" valign="middle">
        We are pleased to offer the twelve volumes of the Published Pennsylvania Archives 3rd Series Tax 
 			Lists.  The 12 volume set is available on a
        <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=3PA1">
         single CD
        </a>
        , and we also offer the volumes in smaller, 
 			county specific
        <a href="docs_new/bookfind.aspx?kw=archives">
         collections
        </a>
        . If you are looking for an ancestor from Pennsylvania in the 1760s, 
 			1770s or 1780s, this full text searchable resource is without equal.  Three additional volumes from 
 			the Published Pennsylvania Archives 3rd Series comprising the
        <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=3P24">
         Warrantees
       of Land
        </a>
        are also available.
       </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
       <td align="left" style="width:41%;height:194px" valign="middle">
        We specialize in electronic reprints of Pennsylvania genealogy books, county history books, 
 			and directories, along with other valuable Pennsylvania genealogy sources. Each CD contains 
 			high quality images of the original pages along with a full text search capability. Our viewer 
 			software, which is provided on each CD, was designed specifically for genealogy researchers and 
 			historians, and runs under Windows 95 thru 7.  Our CDs receive high marks from the experts 
 			(
        <a href="reviews/reviews.aspx">
         read their reviews
        </a>
        ).
       </td>
      </tr>
     </table>
     <table border="0" cellpadding="2" class="HP_XS" style="height:1px" width="100%">
      <tr>
       <td align="left" style="width:30%;height:1px" valign="top">
        Our recent release,
        <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=5PA1">
         Revolutionary
     War
        </a>
        , contains all 8 volumes of the Fifth Series and the first 2 volumes 
 		of the Sixth Series of the Published Pennsylvania Archives.  These volumes are 
 		dedicated almost exclusively to the Pennsylvania officers and soldiers of the 
 		Revolutionary War. This CD represents a unique and valuable research tool for 
 		Pennsylvania genealogy researchers and Revolutionary War enthusiast. Note that 
 		the volumes from the 5th and 6th Series of the Published Pennsylvania Archives 
 		contain extensive updates and corrections to the Pennsylvania Revolutionary War 
 		records originally published in the 2nd &amp; 3rd Series of the Published Pennsylvania Archives.
       </td>
       <td align="center" style="width:18%;height:137px">
        <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=5PA1">
         <img alt="Pennsylvania Military Book Collections on CD-ROM" height="180" src="images/covers/5PA1_30.gif" style="border:0px" width="200"/>
        </a>
        <select class="HP_XSB" id="MilListBox_ID" name="MilListBox_Nm" onchange="rp_ListBox_Military_js();" size="1">
         <option selected="selected" value="0">

         </option>
         <option value="C231">

         </option>

          War of 1812
         </option>
         <option value="5PA1">
          Revolutionary War
         </option>
        </select>
       </td>
       <td align="center" style="width:4%;height:1px" valign="middle">
       </td>
       <td align="center" style="width:18%;height:137px">
        <a href="docs_new/Disc.aspx?disc=1CW1">
         <img alt="Special Book Collections on CD-ROM" height="180" src="images/covers/1CW1_30.gif" style="border:0px" width="200"/>
        </a>
        <select class="HP_XSB" id="ICAListBox_ID" name="ICAListBox_Nm" onchange="rp_ListBox_Inventory_js();" size="1">

          Warren County
         </option>

         </option>
         <option value="1C64">
          Wayne County
         </option>
         <option value="1C65">
          Westmoreland County
         </option>
        </select>
       </td>
       <td align="left" style="width:30%;height:1px" valign="top">
        We are happy to announce the release of a new series for Pennsylvania researchers, "Inventory of the County Archives." 
 			This series is a must for any serious Pennsylvania genealogy researcher. Each Pennsylvania county 
 			volume contains an index and summary of the record set maintained by the county up until the original 
 			publication date (circa. 1940).
        <a href="docs_new/book.aspx?disc=1C01&amp;book=Ada&amp;page=2" target="_blank">
         (sample page)
        </a>
        Unfortunately, only eighteen of the sixty-seven Pennsylvania counties were included in the original series. 
 			The Pennsylvania collection of the Inventory of County Archives now available on CD, should assist in 
 			sparking new ideas for exploring seldom examined and forgotten sources of Pennsylvania county records.
       </td>
      </tr>
